{
  "doc_id": "54219",
  "text": "Advances in the methods for image segmentation and matting [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and cutout have motivated the researchers to provide similar techniques for videos. Chaung et al. proposed video matting [CITATION_3] , where they propagate the user given trimaps for the key frames to the intermediate frames and apply image matting technique on each frame. As discussed by Li et al. [CITATION_4] the dense optical flow can not be accurate determined for all the pixels and therefore errors creep in. Other advanced techniques like Interactive Video Cutout [CITATION_5] , Video Object Cut and Paste [CITATION_6] allow extraction of the object from a video.",
